[ローマンコンクリート]

>従前は材料の質の悪さや混合のずさんさから生じる異物と考えられていた[ライムクラスト]が、他の小さな粒子よりも大きな表面積を持つという特性から、混合コンクリートに生じたひび割れを引き付け、そこに水がしみこむと石灰と反応して溶け出したカルシウムが炭酸カルシウムに変化して乾燥・硬化することで、亀裂を接着し、ひび割れの拡大が防止されるというのです。そして、X線や走査電子顕微鏡による分析で、ローマンコンクリートの石灰には定説されていた消石灰（水酸化カルシウム）ではなく[生石灰]（酸化カルシウム）が使われ、ライムクラストは火山灰や水に生石灰を直接加えて、超高温下で混ぜることで生成されることが明らかになった点でも画期的な研究でした。（という文章を見つけました👀...わからないけど貼っておきます[sume.icon]）[土木の話題39 https://www.kusanosk.co.jp/trivia/column/civil/14607]
ありがとうございます。こちらでも調べてみたところ、どうやら作るのに時間がかかるようですね
https://lab-brains.as-1.co.jp/enjoy-learn/2023/01/43522/#toc_02

Unfortunatedly, My paper was accepeted to International Conference.
The reason why "unfortunatedly" is my poor English skill.
I feel hard to speak, listen English.
And, to write correct English.
To make matters worse, I could not have find my paper is accepted before the last day of requiremet of camera ready version.
That means: my preparing time is less than other participant.
🎉[yosider.icon][はるひ.icon*2][cFQ2f7LRuLYP.icon][seibe.icon]
[GPT-4o.icon]
ここに示された英作文を評価します。

> Unfortunately, my paper was accepted to an International Conference. The reason why I say "unfortunately" is my poor English skill. I find it hard to speak and listen to English, and to write correct English. To make matters worse, I did not find out that my paper was accepted until the last day for the submission of the camera-ready version. That means my preparation time is less than that of other participants.
[*** フィードバック]
1. **Spelling and Grammar**
- "Unfortunatedly" should be "Unfortunately."
これはマジで間違えてた[Summer498.icon]
- "Accepeted" should be "accepted."
これはタイポや[Summer498.icon]
- "Could not have find" should be "could not find."
これは一瞬 find って書いた後で have find に書き直して間違えてる。[Summer498.icon]
- "Requiremet" should be "requirement."
これもタイポや[Summer498.icon]
2. **Punctuation and Structure**
- The phrase "to International Conference" should be "to an International Conference."
- Instead of "The reason why 'unfortunatedly' is my poor English skill," it should be "The reason why I say 'unfortunately' is my poor English skill."
この2つは日本語的な考え方に引っ張られたミス[Summer498.icon]
- The phrase "I feel hard to speak, listen English. And, to write correct English." should be "I find it hard to speak and listen to English, and to write correct English."
箇条書き記法に合わせて書こうとして And, にしちゃってる[Summer498.icon]
, (改行) and の方が良い

- Instead of "I could not have find my paper is accepted before the last day of requiremet of camera ready version," it should be "I did not find out that my paper was accepted until the last day for the submission of the camera-ready version."
わー……抜け落ちてる文法がいっぱいあるわ[Summer498.icon]
- "Participant" should be "participants."
単複間違い[Summer498.icon]
3. **Fluency and Clarity**
- Your ideas are clear, but ensuring proper grammar and punctuation enhances readability and professionalism.
very thanks[Summer498.icon]
Overall, your message is understandable, but correcting the grammatical errors and improving the sentence structure will enhance the fluency of your English writing.
